# YouTube Data API v3 key (used by external video search for short-name
# script disambiguation; falls back to HTML scrape when this isn't set).
#
# Quick setup (~3 minutes):
#
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Create a project (or pick an existing one) — top-left dropdown
# 3. APIs & Services → Library → search "YouTube Data API v3" → Enable
# 4. APIs & Services → Credentials → "+ CREATE CREDENTIALS" → "API key"
# 5. Copy the generated key
# 6. Optional but recommended: click the new key → "Edit API key" →
#    "API restrictions" → restrict to "YouTube Data API v3" only
# 7. Save this file as "yt.api" (drop the .example) and replace the line
#    below with just your key (no quotes, no newlines)
#
# Free quota: 10,000 units/day. Each search costs 100 units = 100 free
# searches/day. The daily scrape uses ~80 searches per run, well under quota.
#
# In GitHub Actions: store the key as a repo secret named `YOUTUBE_API_KEY`
# and the workflow will pass it as an env var (see daily-scrape.yml).
#
# This file is OPTIONAL. Without it, the scraper still works — it just can't
# disambiguate short-name scripts (e.g. "ufo") via video descriptions, so
# ~5–10 of those rows stay in "Missing Demo".
AIzaREPLACE_THIS_WITH_YOUR_API_KEY
